  "local_port": 41144,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I cook manchurian?",
  "response": "Making Manchurian involves two main components: the vegetable balls and the sauce. Here's a basic recipe for vegetarian Manchurian:\n\n### Ingredients:\n\n#### For the Vegetable Manchurian Balls:\n- **Vegetables:** \n  - 1 cup cabbage, finely chopped\n  - 1/2 cup carrots, grated\n  - 1/2 cup capsicum (bell pepper), finely chopped\n  - 1/4 cup spring onions, finely chopped\n- **Binders:**\n  - 1/4 cup all-purpose flour (maida)\n  - 1/4 cup cornflour (cornstarch)\n- **Seasonings:**\n  - 1-2 green chilies, finely chopped\n  - 1 inch ginger, grated\n  - Salt to taste\n- **Oil** for deep frying\n\n#### For the Sauce:\n- **Aromatics:**\n  - 2 tablespoons oil\n  - 1 tablespoon garlic, finely chopped\n  - 1 tablespoon ginger, finely chopped\n  - 1-2 green chilies, slit\n- **Sauce Base:**\n  - 1/4 cup spring onions, chopped\n  - 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n  - 2 tablespoons tomato ketchup\n  - 1 tablespoon chili sauce (adjust to taste)\n  - 1 teaspoon vinegar\n  - 1/4 cup water\n- **Thickener:**\n  - 1 tablespoon cornflour mixed with 2 tablespoons water\n- **Garnish:**\n  - Spring onion greens, chopped\n\n### Instructions:\n\n#### Making the Manchurian Balls:\n1. **Prepare Vegetables:** Combine all the vegetables in a large bowl.\n2. **Mix Ingredients:** Add green chilies, ginger, salt, all-purpose flour, and cornflour to the vegetables. Mix well until combined. The moisture from the vegetables should help bind the mixture.\n3. **Form Balls:** Shape the mixture into small balls. If it's too dry, add a little water. If too wet, add a bit more flour.\n4. **Deep Fry:** Heat oil in a deep frying pan over medium heat. Once hot, fry the vegetable balls in batches until golden brown and cooked through. Remove and drain on paper towels.\n\n#### Making the Sauce:\n1. **Saut\u00e9 Aromatics:** In another pan, heat oil over medium heat. Add garlic, ginger, and green chilies. Saut\u00e9 until aromatic.\n2. **Prepare Sauce:** Add chopped spring onions, soy sauce, tomato ketchup, chili sauce, and vinegar to the pan. Stir and cook for a couple of minutes.\n3. **Thicken Sauce:** Add the cornflour-water mixture and 1/4 cup water to the pan. Stir continuously until the sauce starts to thicken.\n4. **Combine:** Add the fried Manchurian balls to the sauce. Toss to coat the balls evenly.\n5. **Garnish and Serve:** Garnish with chopped spring onion greens and serve hot with fried rice or noodles.\n\nEnjoy your homemade Manchurian! Adjust the spices and sauces according to your taste preference.",
